description:
"Situated Systems" panel with Sarah Brin, Georgina Voss, and Sherri Wasserman at the 2016 Gray Area Festival.

Situated Systems is the inaugural project of the Experimental Research Lab at Autodesk's Pier 9 facility. It explores the industrial and military history of San Francisco, and its role in shaping the regions contemporary technology industries culture and products. Team members and a Lab co-founder will discuss the project, the context, and the relevance of artistic multi-disciplinary research within a corporate design environment.

The Gray Area Festival is four days of conference, performances, workshops, and exhibitions to discuss the impact of art and technology on culture. More at http://grayareafestival.io
